Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the relationship between modal mu calculus and parity games, which are both topics in logic and formal methods. 
- cs.LM (Lattice Mathematics) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the descriptive complexity of formulas, which can be related to lattice theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as model checking is a technique used in programming language verification. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as parity games are a type of game graph, which can be studied in the context of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the semantics of formulas in modal mu calculus, which can be studied in the context of formal languages and automata theory.
